[2026-04-28--19:52:27]User: What is the highest mountain in the world

[2026-04-28--19:52:36]Agent: Mount Everest is the highest mountain above sea level. It sits on the Nepal–China border in the Himalayas and measures about 8,848 meters (29,029 feet), with a newer measurement of 8,848.86 meters (29,031.7 feet) reported in 2020.

Note: If you measure from base to summit, Mauna Kea in Hawaii is taller overall, but its peak is only about 4,200 meters above sea level.
[2026-04-28--19:52:36]User: 
When was it first climbed

[2026-04-28--19:52:44]Agent: Mount Everest was first climbed on May 29, 1953, by Sir Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay. They reached the summit during the British Mount Everest Expedition led by John Hunt, via the southeast ridge (South Col).
